00:30:45.600 --> 00:30:46.756
Pardon me?

00:30:46.756 --> 00:30:48.430
AUDIENCE: Flattered.

00:30:48.430 --> 00:30:50.090
SUSAN ROANE: Oh, flattered.

00:30:50.090 --> 00:30:50.900
Thank you.

00:30:50.900 --> 00:30:52.850
Welcoming and flattered.

00:30:52.850 --> 00:30:55.850
You know what,
anywhere we go where

00:30:55.850 --> 00:30:59.220
we feel welcomed is special.

00:30:59.220 --> 00:31:02.360
But when you go over to
someone, what you're saying

00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:04.470
and why it makes
you feel flattered

00:31:04.470 --> 00:31:07.520
is it's as if you're saying,
you look like someone

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:08.940
I ought to meet.

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:10.790
You look important.

00:31:10.790 --> 00:31:12.780
You look smart.

00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:16.280
You look like you have great
ideas I need to know about.

00:31:16.280 --> 00:31:18.260
It's flattering.

00:31:18.260 --> 00:31:21.220
I doubt that anyone
walks into a room

00:31:21.220 --> 00:31:26.930
for any reason with the purpose
of standing alone and no

00:31:26.930 --> 00:31:28.730
one talking to them.

00:31:28.730 --> 00:31:30.670
I have spoken to CEOs.

00:31:30.670 --> 00:31:34.540
I've spoken to actually
political lobbyists.

00:31:34.540 --> 00:31:37.160
I've spoken to a variety
of groups of people.

00:31:37.160 --> 00:31:40.680
And I can tell you, nobody
walks in a room to stand alone.

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:45.011
Because I don't care how their
celebrity is, what a big kahuna

00:31:45.011 --> 00:31:45.510
they are.

00:31:45.510 --> 00:31:48.750
When someone is standing
by themself in the room,

00:31:48.750 --> 00:31:51.870
their internal voice
is saying, oh my gosh.

00:31:51.870 --> 00:31:52.860
I'm alone.

00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:54.280
I must be a dork.

00:31:54.280 --> 00:31:56.050
That's what we all think.

00:31:56.050 --> 00:31:58.340
So when you go over to
someone, it's welcoming.

00:31:58.340 --> 00:31:59.340
It's acknowledging.

00:31:59.340 --> 00:32:01.770
It's flattering.

00:32:01.770 --> 00:32:02.790
And you heard it here.

00:32:02.790 --> 00:32:04.800
That's what people said.

00:32:04.800 --> 00:32:09.955
Now, those of you who were
the mingling mavens-- a term

00:32:09.955 --> 00:32:12.102
I trademarked, but I'll
share that with you.

00:32:12.102 --> 00:32:14.060
The mingling mavens,
would you raise your hand,

00:32:14.060 --> 00:32:16.940
the people who went
over to other people?

00:32:16.940 --> 00:32:19.070
Can you tell me what
they did that made it--

00:32:19.070 --> 00:32:21.060
besides that I told you
you had to-- but could

00:32:21.060 --> 00:32:26.800
you tell me what they did that
made it OK to go over to them?

00:32:26.800 --> 00:32:28.270
Smiled.

00:32:28.270 --> 00:32:29.920
They smiled.

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:33.890
People, if you have pen
or pencil or your laptops

00:32:33.890 --> 00:32:36.220
or your tablets with
you, write that down.

00:32:36.220 --> 00:32:38.930
This is scientific genius.

00:32:38.930 --> 00:32:40.810
They smiled.

00:32:40.810 --> 00:32:44.260
And what else did they do that
made it OK to go over to them?

00:32:44.260 --> 00:32:46.200
Eye contact.

00:32:46.200 --> 00:32:50.210
Of course, let's just say
someone sees a piece of lint

00:32:50.210 --> 00:32:51.910
on their clothes.

00:32:51.910 --> 00:32:55.077
Do you go over them and go,
it is so nice to meet you?

00:32:55.077 --> 00:32:55.931
No.

00:32:55.931 --> 00:32:59.500
The eye contact, when
you're looking at people,

00:32:59.500 --> 00:33:02.630
they assume you're
interested in meeting them.

00:33:02.630 --> 00:33:05.950
That smile and eye
contact are welcoming.

00:33:05.950 --> 00:33:10.920
They allow people
to feel engaged.

00:33:10.920 --> 00:33:13.620
So if you take
away nothing else,

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:17.280
smile and give eye contact
in every room you're in.

00:33:17.280 --> 00:33:20.180
And I understand there are
some things that are cultural.

00:33:20.180 --> 00:33:21.930
Different cultures
have different thoughts

00:33:21.930 --> 00:33:24.310
about smiling and eye--
well, not about smiling,

00:33:24.310 --> 00:33:26.270
but certainly about eye contact.

00:33:26.270 --> 00:33:29.810
But I'd like you to
embrace that for here.

